A nice Dunkin Donuts; small, but nice. It was quiet during the morning hours when I went (around 7:30 am). The workers were nice, too. Not sure what their heritage was, but their English wasn't the bomb, but that's ok. It is worth mentioning, though. Breakfast bagel was good, as was the hot chocolate (the hot chocolate was better than Panera's if that means anything).
